# What Depends on What — The Dependency Chain

> Nothing exists in isolation. Here's how sectors feed into each other.

```
LAYER 0 — NATURAL RESOURCES (Foundation)
├── Mining & Resources → raw materials for everything
├── Agriculture → food, raw materials for processing
├── Energy → powers ALL other sectors
│
LAYER 1 — TRANSFORMATION (Turn raw into usable)
├── Manufacturing → takes raw materials, produces goods
├── Recycling → takes waste, produces secondary raw materials
├── Agri-Processing → turns crops into products
│
LAYER 2 — MOVEMENT (Move things around)
├── Transport & Logistics → moves goods between all sectors
├── Trading & Import/Export → connects domestic to global markets
│
LAYER 3 — INFRASTRUCTURE (Platforms for activity)
├── Real Estate & Construction → physical spaces for all businesses
├── Energy & Utilities → electricity, water, telecom for everyone
├── Technology → digital infrastructure for modern business
│
LAYER 4 — VALUE DELIVERY (Reach the customer)
├── Services → deliver expertise and labor
├── Hospitality & Food → serve direct consumers
├── Healthcare → serve human health needs
├── Education → build human capital
├── Media & Content → inform, entertain, influence
│
LAYER 5 — ENABLERS (Make everything work)
├── Finance & Investment → capital for all layers
├── Government Contracts → public sector demand
├── IP & Licensing → protect and monetize innovation
│
LAYER 6 — FUTURE (Next frontier)
├── Space & Frontier Tech → depends on ALL layers below
```

```
KEY DEPENDENCY RULES:

→ Every business needs FINANCE (Layer 5)
→ Every business needs ENERGY (Layer 0)
→ Every physical business needs TRANSPORT (Layer 2)
→ Every modern business needs TECHNOLOGY (Layer 3)
→ Every business needs PEOPLE trained by EDUCATION (Layer 4)
→ Every business operates in REAL ESTATE (Layer 3)
→ Manufacturing feeds Services, Trading, and Hospitality
→ Agriculture feeds Manufacturing and Hospitality
→ Recycling feeds back into Manufacturing (circular)
```

